        "params": {
          "text": "<h2>The 4 Cs of food safety</h2><p>The FSA sums up safe food handling in four simple principles known as the <strong>4 Cs</strong>: <strong>Cleaning</strong>, <strong>Cooking</strong>, <strong>Chilling</strong> and avoiding <strong>Cross-contamination</strong>. Together they cover the main ways harmful bacteria are killed, kept out or stopped from spreading.</p><p>Applying the 4 Cs consistently, every time food is handled, is the foundation of good practice in any kitchen.</p>"
        },
