        "params": {
          "title": "<p>Tap a card to flip it</p>",
          "mode": "normal",
          "description": "<p>The 4 Cs of food safety - flip each card to see what it means in practice.</p>",
          "dialogs": [
            {
              "text": "<p>Cleaning</p>",
              "answer": "<p>Keep hands, surfaces and equipment clean. Wash hands thoroughly with warm water and soap, and clean and disinfect food-contact surfaces before and after preparing food.</p>",
              "tips": {}
            },
            {
              "text": "<p>Cooking</p>",
              "answer": "<p>Cook food thoroughly so harmful bacteria are killed. Aim for a core temperature of 75C, and check that food is piping hot all the way through, especially poultry, mince and reheated dishes.</p>",
              "tips": {}
            },
            {
              "text": "<p>Chilling</p>",
              "answer": "<p>Keep chilled food cold to slow bacterial growth. Store it in a fridge at 5C or below, cool cooked food quickly, and never leave perishable food standing at room temperature.</p>",
              "tips": {}
            },
            {
              "text": "<p>Cross-contamination</p>",
              "answer": "<p>Stop harmful bacteria spreading from raw food to ready-to-eat food. Use separate boards and utensils, store raw meat below other foods, and wash hands between tasks.</p>",
              "tips": {}
            }
          ],
